cookies_policy_content:
This Cookies Policy explains what cookies are and how we use them. You should read this policy so you can understand what type of information we collect, how we use the information, and how you can control the collection of information.

What are cookies?

Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device by a website when you visit it. They store information about your browsing activity on the website, including your preferences (such as language and font size) and browsing history (the pages you have viewed).

What types of cookies do we use?

We use a variety of cookies on our website, including:

Essential cookies: These cookies are strictly necessary for the operation of our website. They allow you to navigate the website and use its features, such as accessing secure areas of the website.

Performance cookies: These cookies collect information about how you use our website, such as the pages you visit and how long you spend on each page. This information helps us to improve the performance of our website and to provide a better user experience.

Functionality cookies: These cookies allow our website to remember your preferences (such as your language and location) and to provide you with enhanced and more personalized features.

Targeting cookies: These cookies are used to deliver advertising that is relevant to you and your interests. They may also be used to limit the number of times you see an advertisement as well as to measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.

How can you control cookies?

You can control and/or delete cookies as you wish. You can delete all cookies that are already on your computer and you can prevent cookies from being placed. However, if you do this, you may have to manually adjust some preferences every time you visit a website and some services and functionalities may not work properly.

Changes to this Cookies Policy

We may update this Cookies Policy from time to time. You are advised to periodically review this policy for any changes.

dispute_resolution_content:
This procedure outlines the steps involved in resolving disputes arising between [Company Name] and any other party.

1. Informal Discussion:

The party initiating the dispute should submit a written complaint outlining the issue and desired resolution.
This complaint can be submitted to the designated representative at [Company Name] (e.g., Customer Service Manager, Project Manager).
The designated representative will attempt to resolve the issue through informal discussion with the other party.

2. Mediation (Optional):

If an informal resolution cannot be reached, both parties may agree to participate in mediation.
A neutral third-party mediator will facilitate communication and attempt to guide the parties towards a mutually agreeable solution.
The mediator does not have the authority to impose a decision.

3. Final Resolution:

If mediation is unsuccessful or declined, the following options are available:
For [Company Name] customers: You may pursue remedies outlined in your contract or applicable law.
For other parties: The dispute may be referred to [Arbitration/Court/ as specified in your contract].

Timelines:

A timeframe for responding to complaints at each stage can be specified here (e.g., 10 business days for informal discussion response).

Confidentiality:

All discussions and information related to the dispute will be treated confidentially by all parties involved.

Exceptions:

This procedure may not apply to certain types of disputes as specified by law or contract.

Review:

This Dispute Resolution Procedure may be reviewed and updated periodically by [Company Name].

Contact Information:

Include contact details for the designated representative at [Company Name] for initiating the dispute resolution process.
community_standards_content:
Welcome!

These Community Standards are in place to foster a safe, respectful, and enjoyable environment for everyone. By participating in our community, you agree to follow these guidelines.

Be Kind and Respectful:

- Treat others with dignity and courtesy.
- Disagreements are okay, but keep it civil. No personal attacks, insults, or flaming.
- Everyone has a right to their opinion. Listen to others and be open to different perspectives.

Keep it Safe:

- Do not share personal information about yourself or others.
- Avoid posting content that promotes violence, hate speech, or illegal activity.
- Report any suspicious activity or content that makes you uncomfortable.

Be Honest and Authentic:

- Do not impersonate others or spread misinformation.
- Avoid spamming or posting irrelevant content.
- Be truthful in your interactions with others.

Content Guidelines:

- Refrain from posting content that is sexually suggestive, violent, or gory.
- Use profanity sparingly, if at all.
- Keep it relevant to the community topic.

Consequences of Violation:

We reserve the right to remove content that violates these standards. Repeated violations may lead to temporary or permanent suspension from the community.

Reporting Violations:

If you see something, say something! Report any violations of these standards to a moderator.

Thank you for being a part of our community!
about_us_desc: SellOut was created to be your one-stop platform for buying & selling and providing services. Our goal is to make SellOut a revolutionary platform designed to empower both buyers and sellers, creating a vibrant online marketplace for products and services. We believe in connecting people seamlessly and fostering a thriving community of individuals passionate about E-commerce. We envision a world where buying and selling are effortless experiences and accessible to everyone all around the world. SellOut aims to be the go-to platform for individuals seeking diverse products, exceptional services and a hassle-free trading journey.
meet_sellout_team_desc: Sellout is driven by a passionate team of individuals dedicated to making your online buying & selling and services experience exceptional.
zubair_description: Zubair's vision for SellOut stems from his own experience navigating the complexities of online commerce. He saw a need for a platform that simplified the process, catered to both buyers and sellers, and fostered a sense of community. His leadership and innovative spirit guide SellOut's growth and development. His determination and willpower wil ensure the success of the company.
abdul_description: Abdul's is the creative force behind SellOut's infrastructure and functionality. He translates complex concepts into intuitive and user- friendly features for everyone. He is constantly finding ways to improve the platform and keeping up with the latest trends.
hammad_description: Hammad's dedication and passion ensures the Front- End of SellOut remains clean and maintainable. He focuses on building responsive, accessible interfaces while learning and growing under the senior development team.
ahmed_description: Ahmed's commitment and attention to detail has helped structure SellOut's Back-End development...
rafah_description: Ayhab's dedication and passion ensures the Front-End of SellOut remains world class with a keen eye for detail. He is responsible for the overall look and feel and smooth functionalities of the Sellout user experience and is always finding ways to keep the platform simple and easy to use.
